o study music and popular culture. In addition, he traces the history of West African possession religion from Africa to the diaspora to its integration into American popular music in such genres as the blues, rock and roll, and contemporary musical youth subcultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPopular culturexReligious aspects. 0aPopular musicxReligious aspects. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479875238.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479875238423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479875238/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles